Windows:
Download, Install Java & set-up env var
The JDK software is installed on your computer, for example, at C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.x.x_xx. 
Set JAVA_HOME:
Right click My Computer and select Properties.
On the Advanced tab, select Environment Variables, and then edit JAVA_HOME to point to where the JDK software is located, for example, C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.x.x_xx

Download Apache Maven and set=up env var
M2_HOME=C:\Program Files\Apache Software Foundation\apache-maven-x.x.x 
M2=%M2_HOME%\bin 
MAVEN_OPTS=-Xms256m -Xmx512m

Download Intellij(preferrable) editor(or your choice)
